Course Description

  • This will be a full English course.

  • We will use English everywhere (textbook, slides, homework, exam etc.) except conversation.

  • Chinese homework and exam will not be accepted and get no score!

Course Requirements

  • Homework
    • 2 Problem Sets
    • All homework should be typed (and stapled)
    • Work that is not typed (or stapled) gets an automatic discount of 30%
    • Assignments not turned in by the due date will be penalized 10 points for each day it is late
    • Students are strongly encouraged to work in groups. However, each student is responsible of writing up his or her own problem set.

Course Requirements

  • Project
    • 1 Project
    • You need to collect the data and do some analysis in group.
    • You will be asked to comment on others work.

Course Requirements

  • Exams
    • 1 final exam
    • Final date: 20 Nov, Lec 5-6, D9-A315
    • Any cheater will get a grade of zero. A stronger punishment is not ruled out.

Grading Policy

  • The weights for the final score will be as follows:
    • Problem sets: 30%
    • Projects: 20%( 15% + 5% )
    • Final exam: 50%
  • I reserve the right to raise the final score, but I will not lower them.

Course Schedule

  • The material of the textbook is summarized below.
    • Part1: International Trade Theory
    • Part2: International Trade Policy
    • Part3: Exchange Rates and Open-Economy macroeconomics
    • Part4: International Macroeconomic Policy

  • We will definitely cover parts I and try to finish part II.

  • You could find the necessary materials in the course website: bayeswhu.github.io/teaching/trade.html

Questions?
